{{Distinguish|動物權利}}
{{NoteTA
|1=zh-cn:荷尔斯泰因牛; zh-tw:荷斯登牛;
|2=zh-cn:圣艾蒂安; zh-tw:聖德田;
|3=zh-hk:質素; zh-tw:品質;
}}

'''動物福利'''（{{lang-en|'''animal welfare'''}}），或譯'''動物福祉'''<ref>{{Cite web|title=畜牧產業新趨勢：採取「人道飼養」達成動物福祉，更有助於提升營收！|url=https://www.seinsights.asia/article/3291/3272/5506|accessdate=2021-04-01|author=廖震元|date=2018-06-07|publisher=社企流|language=zh-tw|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120093629/https://www.seinsights.asia/article/3291/3272/5506|archive-date=2021-01-20|dead-url=no|quote=人道飼養是近年國際間重視的議題，但在台灣，許多人對此觀念仍非常陌生。人道飼養的根基建立在「動物福祉」上，主要的訴求為讓動物有 5 大自由（five freedoms），當動物飼養符合了這些條件，才算是符合了人道飼養的基本要求。}}</ref>，是指非人類[[動物|動物]]的（生活）福祉。動物福利的正式標準因環境而異，但主要由動物福利團體、[[立法机关|立法]]者和[[學者|學者]]進行辯論。<ref>{{cite web|title=Animals are not things: A view on animal welfare based on neurological complexity|url=http://www.humanities.uci.edu/collective/hctr/trans-scripts/2013/2013_03_10.pdf|access-date=20 December 2013|last=Grandin|first=Temple|year=2013|work=Trans-Scripts 3: An Interdisciplinary Online Journal in Humanities And Social Sciences at UC Irvine|publisher=[[UC_Irvine|UC Irvine]]|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20140819053847/http://www.humanities.uci.edu/collective/hctr/trans-scripts/2013/2013_03_10.pdf|archive-date=19 August 2014|author-link=Temple Grandin|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="Hewson">{{cite journal|title=What is animal welfare? Common definitions and their practical consequences|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_the-canadian-veterinary-journal_2003-06_44_6/page/496|last=Hewson|first=C.J.|journal=The Canadian Veterinary Journal|issue=6|year=2003|volume=44|pages=496–99|pmc=340178|pmid=12839246}}</ref> 動物福利科學使用諸如壽命、疾病、免疫抑制、行為、生理和繁殖等衡量標準<ref>{{cite journal|title=Animal welfare: concepts and measurement|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-animal-science_1991-10_69_10/page/4167|last=Broom|first=D. M.|journal=[[Journal_of_Animal_Science|Journal of Animal Science]]|issue=10|doi=10.2527/1991.69104167x|year=1991|volume=69|pages=4167–75|pmid=1778832}}</ref>，儘管關於這些中哪些最能代表動物福利存在爭議。

對動物福利的尊重通常基於這樣一種信念，即非人類動物是有[[感情|知覺]]的，應該考慮它們的福祉或[[痛苦|痛苦]]，尤其是當它們在人類的飼養環境中。<ref>{{cite web|title=Draft of the Universal Declaration on Animal Welfare|url=http://media.animalsmatter.org/media/resources/en/en_draft.pdf|publisher=media.animalmatter.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120227004725/http://media.animalsmatter.org/media/resources/en/en_draft.pdf|archive-date=27 February 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> 這些問題可能包括動物如何被屠宰作為食物、它們如何用於科學研究、它們如何被飼養（作為寵物，或在動物園、農場、馬戲團等），以及人類活動如何影響野生物種的福祉和生存。

對動物福利概念的批評有兩種形式，來自截然相反的立場。歷史上一些思想家所持的一種觀點認為，人類對動物沒有任何[[責任|責任]]。另一種觀點是基於[[動物權利|動物權利]]的立場，即動物不應被視為財產，人類對動物的任何使用都是不可接受的。因此，一些動物權利支持者認為，更好的動物福利的觀念促進了對動物的持續和增加的剝削。<ref>{{cite book|last=Garner|first=R.|year=2005|title=Animal Ethics|url=https://archive.org/details/animalethics0000garn|url-access=registration|publisher=[[Polity_Press|Polity Press]]}}</ref><ref name="Regan 1983">{{cite book|last=Regan|first=T.|year=1983|title=The Case for Animal Rights|url=https://archive.org/details/caseforanimalrig00regarich|url-access=registration|publisher=University of California Press|isbn=9780520049048}}</ref> 因此，一些當局將動物福利和動物權利視為兩個對立的立場。<ref name="Francione 1995">{{cite book|last=Francione|first=G.|year=1995|title=Animals, Property, and the Law|publisher=[[Temple_University_Press|Temple University Press]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=What is Animal Welfare and why is it important?|url=http://www.naiaonline.org/articles/article/what-is-animal-welfare-and-why-is-it-important|access-date=27 June 2014|publisher=National Animal Interest Alliance|archive-date=2021-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221131735/https://www.naiaonline.org/articles/article/what-is-animal-welfare-and-why-is-it-important|dead-url=no}}</ref> 其他人將動物福利的收益視為朝著動物權利邁進的漸進步驟。

現代[[神經科學|神經科學]]領域的主要觀點是，即使在人類中也存在[[意識|意識]]定義的哲學問題，但意識存在於非人類動物中。<ref>{{cite web|title=The Cambridge Declaration on Consciousness|url=http://fcmconference.org/img/CambridgeDeclarationOnConsciousness.pdf|access-date=26 May 2015|archive-date=2013-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109230457/http://fcmconference.org/img/CambridgeDeclarationOnConsciousness.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Scientists Finally Conclude Nonhuman Animals Are Conscious Beings|url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/animal-emotions/201208/scientists-finally-conclude-nonhuman-animals-are-conscious-beings|access-date=26 May 2015}}</ref> 然而，有些人仍然認為意識是一個哲學問題，可能永遠不會得到科學解決。<ref>{{cite web|title=Do animals have consciousness?|url=http://scienceline.org/2015/03/do-animals-have-consciousness/|access-date=26 May 2015|date=6 March 2015|archive-date=2021-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211221131715/https://scienceline.org/2015/03/do-animals-have-consciousness/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 值得注意的是，一項新研究成功地克服了在經驗上測試這個問題的一些困難，並設計了一種獨特的方法來將動物的意識與無意識[[知覺|知覺]]分離。<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Disentangling perceptual awareness from nonconscious processing in rhesus monkeys (Macaca mulatta)|first1=Moshe Shay|last2=Monte|first2=Olga Dal|date=2021-04-13|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|issue=15|doi=10.1073/pnas.2017543118|volume=118|pages=e2017543118|language=en|issn=0027-8424|pmc=8053918|pmid=33785543|last3=Fagan|first3=Nicholas A.|last4=Dunham|first4=Yarrow|last5=Hassin|first5=Ran R.|last6=Chang|first6=Steve W. C.|last7=Santos|first7=Laurie R.|last1=Ben-Haim}}</ref> 在[[恒河猴|恒河猴]]中進行的這項研究中，研究人員建立了[[實驗|實驗]]，預測與有意識與無意識感知[[刺激_(生理学)|刺激]]完全相反的[[行為|行為]]結果。引人注目的是，猴子的行為表現出這些完全相反的特徵，就像在研究中測試的有意識和無意識的人類一樣。<ref name=":0" />

動物福利包括身體[[健康|健康]]、自然行為的可行性（“正常行為”）和動物的[[情緒|情緒]]健康。<ref>I. J. H. Duncan, D. Fraser: ''Understanding animal welfare.'' In: M. C. Appleby, B. O. Hughes (Hrsg.): ''Animal Welfare.'' Wallingford, UK 1997, S. 19–31.</ref> 

動物福利關鍵取決於飼養者是否對動物友好，即是否滿足動物的需求。動物福利被描述為飼養環境和動物處理的可衡量標準，“環境條件在多大程度上為動物提供了避免[[痛苦|痛苦]]和損害以及確保福祉的先決條件”。<ref>Ute Knierim: ''Beurteilung der Tiergerechtheit – Konzepte und Begriffsdefinitionen'' (Begleittexte zum Vortrag, [https://www.ktbl.de/fileadmin/user_upload/Allgemeines/Download/Tiergerechtheit/Beurteilung-der-Tiergerechtheit.pdf online] {{Wayback|url=https://www.ktbl.de/fileadmin/user_upload/Allgemeines/Download/Tiergerechtheit/Beurteilung-der-Tiergerechtheit.pdf |date=20210712111611 }}), S. 3–5. Vgl. Ute Knierim: ''Grundsätzliche ethologische Überlegungen zur Beurteilung der Tiergerechtheit bei Nutztieren.'' In: ''Deutsche Tierärztliche Wochenschrift'' 109, 2002, S. 261–266.</ref> 關於哪些飼養條件和程序不被評估為動物友好的決定，取決於科學[[知識|知識]]水平，也取決於社會[[偏好|偏好]]。[[立法机关|立法機構]]定義了動物福利相關法規的最低要求。

== 背景 ==
動物與[[人類|人類]]一樣，有生理、環境、行為、心理和社群五大類需求，這些需求的滿足與否，顯示動物福利{{noteTag|name=福利註釋|1=“福利”係指動物生理、行為和心理的需求獲得滿足的程度。}}是否良好<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.east.org.tw/ext/animal-action.east.org.tw/modules/tinyd0/index87f1.html?id=14 |title = 認識「動物福利」 |author = 台灣動物社會研究會 |date =  |publisher = 社團法人台灣動物社會研究會 |language = zh-tw |accessdate = 2020-06-23 |quote = 科學研究發現，許多動物與人類一樣，都有完備神經系統、痛覺及趨樂避苦的本能反應，或判斷與抉擇，也各有其生理、環境、行為、心理和社群上五大類別的需求以供生存及繁衍。這些需求的滿足與否，顯示其動物福利是否良好。瞭解動物個體的需求，是維護動物福利的第一步。動物的需求，會因物種、品種，甚至個體而有不同 |archive-date = 2020-09-15 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200915055815/https://www.east.org.tw/ext/animal-action.east.org.tw/modules/tinyd0/index87f1.html?id=14 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。讓動物「滿足這些需求的自由」，稱為動物福利的五大自由。

=== 起源 ===
談論動物福利，得從[[英國皇家防止虐待動物協會|英國皇家防止虐待動物協會]]（RSPCA）談起。在19世紀，[[英國|英國]]存在鬥狗、鬥熊等殘忍的娛樂活動，也有使用殘酷方式驅趕[[牲畜|牲畜]]等經濟動物<ref name="農傳媒">{{cite news |language = zh-tw |author = 李朝全 |coauthors =  |url = https://agriharvest.tw/archives/4725 |title = 臺灣動物福利發展歷程溯源，展望友善動物國度 |publisher = 農傳媒 |pages =  |date = 2019-02-19 |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |archive-date = 2020-10-31 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201031043925/https://agriharvest.tw/archives/4725 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。1822年起，[[英國國會|英國國會]]議員理查·馬丁（Richard Martin）於國會倡議設立草案<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.branchcollective.org/?ps_event=richard-martins-act |title = Richard Martin’s Act |author =  |date =  |publisher = BRANCH: Britain, Representation, and Nineteenth-Century History |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-24 |quote = On 22 July 1822, Richard Martin’s Act — or the “Act to prevent the cruel and improper treatment of Cattle” — becomes law in Parliament. |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918042000/http://www.branchcollective.org/?ps_event=richard-martins-act |dead-url = no }}</ref>，防止虐待{{noteTag|name=虐待註釋|1=“虐待”意指任何故意，或因疏忽，而造成動物非必要的痛苦或緊迫之行為。}}[[牛|牛]]、[[馬|馬]]及[[綿羊|綿羊]]，其理論是要顯示人類仁愛、仁慈的行為。他於1824年更成為英國防止虐待動物協會的創辦人之一<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.animallaw.info/article/history-rspca |title = The History of the RSPCA |author =  |date = 1972 |publisher = Michigan State University College of Law |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-24 |quote = Resolved also :<br>That a Committee be appointed to adopt measures for Inspecting the Markets and Streets of the Metropolis, the Slaughter Houses, the conduct of Coachmen, etc.- etc, consisting of the following Gentlemen:<br>T F Buxton Esqr. MP, Richard Martin Esqr., MP, Sir James Graham, L B Allen Esqr., C C Wilson Esqr., Jno. Brogden Esqr., Alderman Brydges, A E Kendal Esqr., E Lodge Esqr., J Martin Esqr. T G Meymott Esqr. |archive-date = 2021-02-05 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210205064241/https://www.animallaw.info/article/history-rspca |dead-url = no }}</ref>。1840年，[[維多利亞女皇|維多利亞女皇]]賜予該會「皇家」封號<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rspca.org.uk/whatwedo/whoweare/history |title = The origins & history of the RSPCA |author =  |date =  |publisher = RSPCA |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-24 |quote = Back then we were the SPCA - Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals. Royal patronage followed in 1837 and Queen Victoria gave permission to add the royal R in 1840, making us the RSPCA as we're known worldwide today. |archive-date = 2021-02-04 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210204135018/https://www.rspca.org.uk/whatwedo/whoweare/history |dead-url = no }}</ref>。該會透過會員的捐助，募請大批調查人員，尋找出虐待{{noteTag|name=虐待註釋|2=“虐待”意指任何故意，或因疏忽，而造成動物非必要的痛苦或緊迫之行為。}}動物的人，搜集證據，並向執法機構舉報。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rspca.org.au/what-we-do/our-role-enforcing-law |title = Our role in enforcing the law |author =  |date =  |publisher = RSPCA |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-24 |quote = RSPCA member Societies enforce state and territory animal welfare legislation through their Inspectorate functions. Where incidences of animal cruelty or animal welfare concerns are reported, our Inspectors have the power to investigate and prosecute those involved. |archive-date = 2021-02-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210214084230/https://www.rspca.org.au/what-we-do/our-role-enforcing-law |dead-url = no }}</ref>

=== 五大自由 ===
1965年，英國政府為回應社會訴求<ref name="EAST">{{Cite web |url = https://www.east.org.tw/action/1229 |title = 動物福利科學－簡介與簡史 |author =  |date = 2005-03-26 |publisher = 社團法人台灣動物社會研究會 |language = zh-tw |accessdate = 2020-06-22 |quote = 但可能很少人知道，這五大自由是英國政府農場動物福利委員會（FAWC）於1992年所提出，而其前身則是1965年回應Ruth Harrison所著《動物機器（Animal Machine）》一書而成立之「布蘭貝爾委員會」，於訪查各地農場並聽取證詞之後，針對所有農場動物所提的建議：須有「足夠的自由」——能夠輕易轉身、整理毛髮，站、躺以及伸展四肢。 |archive-date = 2020-09-17 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200917225740/https://www.east.org.tw/action/1229 |dead-url = no }}</ref>，委任羅傑·布拉姆貝爾（Roger Brambell）教授對農場動物的福利事宜進行研究<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.canr.msu.edu/news/an_animal_welfare_history_lesson_on_the_five_freedoms |title = The Five Freedoms: A history lesson in animal care and welfare |author = Tina Conklin |date = 2019-09-06 |publisher = Michigan State University |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-26 |quote = To understand the importance of the Five Freedoms and why there were developed, let’s turn back to 1964 when Ruth Harrison, a British woman, wrote “Animal Machines.” The book described intensive livestock and poultry farming practices of the time. The outcry of the British public regarding the information in the book prompted the British government to appoint a committee to look into the welfare of farm animals. In 1965, the committee, chaired by professor Roger Brambell presented the 85-page “Report of the Technical Committee to Inquire into the Welfare of Animals Kept under Intensive Livestock Husbandry Systems,” which became known as “The Brambell Report.” |archive-date = 2020-12-27 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201227055248/https://www.canr.msu.edu/news/an_animal_welfare_history_lesson_on_the_five_freedoms |dead-url = no }}</ref>。根據研究結果，於1967年成立農場動物福利諮詢委員會，1979年改組為農場動物福利委員會（Farm Animal Welfare Committee, FAWC），委員會提出動物都會有渴求「轉⾝、弄乾⾝體、起立、躺下和伸展四肢」的⾃由<ref>{{cite news |language = zh-tw |author = 高維奇 |coauthors =  |url = http://www.tanews.org.tw/info/15030 |title = 李朝全談「動物福利的演進與因應」 |publisher = 台灣動物新聞網 |pages =  |date = 2018-06-29 |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |archive-date = 2020-06-29 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200629182936/http://www.tanews.org.tw/info/15030 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。1992年，由該會提出「五大自由」的原則<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.fawec.org/media/com_lazypdf/pdf/fs1-en.pdf |title = WHAT IS ANIMAL WELFARE? |author = X Manteca |date = 2012-06-01 |publisher = FAWEC |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |quote = In accordance with the ‘Five Freedoms’ principle, an animal’s welfare is ensured when the following five conditions are met (FAWC, 1992; 1993) |archive-date = 2020-09-23 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200923155029/https://www.fawec.org/media/com_lazypdf/pdf/fs1-en.pdf |dead-url = no }}</ref>。FAWC每年針對一種畜牧產業調查，深入研究動物福利問題，再提報告供農業部長參考。該報告會描述畜牧業的實際狀況，現存動物福利問題，與相應的原由，並提出短、中、長期的三種建議。FAWC深入溝通、攜手合作的方式十分有效，獲各國效法、類似組織接連成立。<ref name="NGO心視野">{{Cite journal|author= 李淵百|author2= |author3= |url= https://www.taiwanngo.tw/p/405-1000-20735,c445.php?Lang=zh-tw|title= 如何從教育來改進台灣的農場動物福利|journal= 台灣動物之聲|year= 2013|volume= |issue= 60|pages= |access-date= 2020-08-09|archive-date= 2020-09-15|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200915053340/https://www.taiwanngo.tw/p/405-1000-20735,c445.php?Lang=zh-tw|dead-url= no}}</ref>

根據[[世界動物衛生組織|世界動物衛生組織]]《陸生動物衛生法典》（TAHC），動物福利是指，與動物生死狀況相關的生理、心理狀態，以科學為基礎，並採用五大自由推動相關福利，作為動物健康與食品安全之依據。世界動物衛生組織（OIE）於1924年成立，主要任務為制定國際貿易動物衛生標準，使[[世界貿易組織|世界貿易組織]]（WTO）有法可依。2004年，世界動物衛生組織首次召開全球動物福利會議，並在隔年出版《世界動物衛生組織動物福利標準》（OIE Standards on Animal Welfare），供會員國使用。<ref name="農傳媒" />
[[File:TomRegan2.jpg|thumb]]
* 免於缺乏[[營養|營養]]、[[飢餓|飢餓]]與乾渴的自由<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://everylivingthing.ca/1-freedom-from-thirst-and-hunger/ |title = 1 – Freedom from Thirst and Hunger |author = Melissa Logan |date = 2017-05-03 |publisher = Alberta SPCA |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |quote = How much food and water does the animal in your care need? The answer to this question depends on a number of factors. The species of the animal, their age, size, health status, and activity level are all factors that can affect how much they should be eating and drinking. Older dogs, for example should be eating less food than younger dogs, because they aren’t as active, and young puppies need to eat a lot of food so that they can grow, run and play. In addition, a cow that has a calf needs to drink a lot of water so that they can supply enough milk to their calf, whereas a cow without a calf doesn’t have to drink as much. |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918005745/https://everylivingthing.ca/1-freedom-from-thirst-and-hunger/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>：<br>清淨的飲水及維持健康與活力所需之食物，能夠供應無虞。
* 免於[[生理|生理]]上及[[心理|心理]]上不適的自由<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://everylivingthing.ca/2-freedom-from-discomfort/ |title = 2 – Freedom from Discomfort |author = Melissa Logan |date = 2017-05-10 |publisher = Alberta SPCA |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |quote = What is considered to be a comfortable resting area? Well, it depends! Different animal species vary in how they feel comfortable. For example, dogs might be perfectly happy resting on a dog bed on the floor, and cats may prefer to rest on the top level of a cat tree, or even in a box where they feel hidden and safe. Large animals like cows prefer to rest in areas with at least enough space to be able to lie down, turn around, and get back up again. They also like areas that are cushioned, so that its more comfortable and they don’t hurt their knees. Cold blooded animal such as snakes and lizards like the ability to rest under the glow of the sun or a heat lamp. Some animals like rabbits, rats, and hamsters feel most safe resting in hide boxes where they can’t be easily seen. |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918000938/https://everylivingthing.ca/2-freedom-from-discomfort/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>：<br>提供適當庇護環境，以及舒適的休息場所，溫度與氣候。
* 免於[[疾病|疾病]]與傷害的自由<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://everylivingthing.ca/3-freedom-from-pain-injury-and-disease/ |title = 3- Freedom from Pain, Injury, and Disease |author = Melissa Logan |date = 2017-05-17 |publisher = Alberta SPCA |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |quote = Veterinarians have special training that helps them determine what is causing pain in animals, which is a pretty tough job since animals can’t tell them what hurts! Once they know what is causing the pain, they can treat the animal, helping them to feel better. Just like people need to visit doctors, animals require checkups from their veterinarian! Going to the veterinarian on a regular basis will keep your pet healthy as it allows the veterinarian to find problems before they become troublesome. By catching problems before they start, your pet has a better chance to stay healthy. In fact, taking your pet to the veterinarian to get vaccinated is a very important part of being a responsible pet owner. Certain diseases, like rabies are quite contagious and can make animals very sick. |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918032832/https://everylivingthing.ca/3-freedom-from-pain-injury-and-disease/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>：<br>提供預防、迅速診斷與疾病治療。
* 免於[[恐懼|恐懼]]與[[緊迫|緊迫]]的自由<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://everylivingthing.ca/4-freedom-from-fear-and-distress/ |title = 4- Freedom from Fear and Distress |author = Melissa Logan |date = 2017-05-26 |publisher = Alberta SPCA |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |quote = Just like humans, animals are also able to experience fear. Fear is not only unpleasant, but it can also have an impact on an animal’s health. An animal that is constantly exposed to conditions that make them fearful will experience poor mental and physical health. Mentally, the animal will become very alert and will regularly feel overwhelmed and worried. Physically, the animal may experience digestion issues, heart problems, and difficulty sleeping and eating. It’s important that we treat animals well and provide them with conditions that prevent them from feeling fear. |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918045023/https://everylivingthing.ca/4-freedom-from-fear-and-distress/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>：<br>確保各種環境及對待不會造成精神上的痛苦。
* 自然表現行為的自由<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://everylivingthing.ca/5-freedom-to-express-normal-behavior/ |title = 5 – Freedom to Express Normal Behavior |author = Melissa Logan |date = 2017-06-06 |publisher = Alberta SPCA |language = en |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |quote = What is considered to be “normal” behavior varies from species to species. For example, coprophagy, the act of eating feces, is a very normal and essential behavior in rabbits however, it would be considered an abnormal behavior for cats. Similarly, chattering, the act of making a chirping sound at birds, is a completely normal behavior in cat but it would be considered an odd behavior if a horse was found chattering at birds! Therefore, it is important to do your research on what is considered normal behavior for your animal species. By knowing what your animal’s normal behavior is and allowing them to express it, you will be helping to improve their well-being. In addition, knowing what is an abnormal behavior for your animal will allow you to recognize when something is wrong, whether it is a result of stress, sickness, or general discontent. |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918073343/https://everylivingthing.ca/5-freedom-to-express-normal-behavior/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>：<br>提供足夠空間、適當設施以及同類動物伴侶。

=== 六類動物 ===
{{see|野生動物|伴侶動物|實驗動物|免於殘忍|3R原則}}

[[世界動物保護協會|世界動物保護協會]]《動物福利普世宣言》中，主要原則第3－8條：規範和管理「野生動物{{noteTag|name=野生動物註釋|1=“野生動物”包括未被人類所馴化的任何動物。}}」、「依人動物」、「為食物、產製品、或勞力而飼養的動物」、「同伴動物{{noteTag|name=同伴動物註釋|1=“同伴動物”意指於各地文化脈絡中，傳統上即為人類的同伴，且無論是刻意與否，其係為此目的而被繁殖的動物。}}」、「用於運動與娛樂的動物」和「科學研究中的活體動物」，其原則適用分為六類動物。在主要原則第4條依人動物（Human-dependent animals）的部分，內文重申了『五大自由』，並記載任何動物的創傷、疾病或緊迫，若嚴重到必須持續遭受痛苦時，[[獸醫|獸醫]]或其他合格人士應被授權，得以[[人道|人道]]方式讓動物[[死亡|死亡]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.east.org.tw/publication/6060 |title = 動物福利普世宣言（UNIVERSAL DECLARATION FOR THE WELFARE OF ANIMALS） |author = 朱增宏 |date = 2001-06-01 |publisher = 台灣動物社會研究會 |language = zh-tw |accessdate = 2020-07-02 |quote = PROCLAIMS this Universal Declaration for the Welfare of Animals as a common standard of achievement for all peoples and all nations, to strive by all appropriate means to promote respect for these principles and by progressive measures, national and international, to secure their universal and effective recognition and observance. |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918020258/https://www.east.org.tw/publication/6060 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

=== 與動物權之差異 ===
{{see also|動物權利}}

動物權出自1870年代出現的反對[[活體解剖|活體解剖]]運動<ref name="EAST" />。動物權（animal rights）一詞源自於[[動物倫理|動物倫理]]（animal ethics），相關議題探討主要涉及[[命題|命題]]為，人類以外的動物是否享有神聖不可剝奪的[[權利|權利]]？動物權最早並非廣泛地適對所有動物，而僅限於那些對於生理[[疼痛|疼痛]]或心理痛苦有感知能力的動物，持此立場的代表性人物當屬[[傑瑞米·邊沁|傑瑞米·邊沁]]（Jeremy Bentham）。傑瑞米·邊沁是18世紀英國政治哲學家，其最常被引用的兩句話為：長有幾條[[腿|腿]]、[[皮膚|皮膚]]是否長有絨毛、是否長有[[尾巴|尾巴]]，皆不能構成剝奪一個生靈享有與人類同等被對待的原因；問題不在於動物能否[[思考|思考]]，也不在於動物能否[[說話|說話]]，在於牠們能否感受到[[痛苦|痛苦]]。<ref name="動物權">{{Cite web |url = https://hre.pro.edu.tw/article/3853 |title = 動物權或動物福利？ 概念內涵與動保政策意涵之區辨 |author = 王毓正 |date = 2019-02-27 |publisher = 人權教育諮詢暨資源中心 |language = zh-tw |accessdate = 2020-06-27 |quote = 對於具有感知能力之生物給予特別的保護，或可說是目前動物權與動物福利（Animal welfare）兩派論述的共同基礎。換言之，無論動物權擁護者或動物福利擁護者皆支持應避免使具有感知能力之動物遭受痛苦，或是應該促進這類動物的福利；只不過動物權擁護者並不滿足僅避免使這類動物遭受痛苦或為其促進福利，而是希望動物固有的尊嚴亦可能受到法律的肯定，並且具有權利主體之地位。 |archive-date = 2020-09-15 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200915053111/https://hre.pro.edu.tw/article/3853 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

動物權擁護者不滿足於避免使上述動物遭受痛苦，或為其促進福利，而希望動物固有尊嚴受到[[法律|法律]]保障，並且具有[[權利主體|權利主體]]的地位。假使完全貫徹其思想，則應該以[[道德|道德]]方式對待動物，動物本來就享有此等權利。例如：[[湯姆·雷根|湯姆·雷根]]（Tom Reagan）即主張，動物有天賦價值，動物與人有完全相同的道德地位，因此人類不能主張有更高的利益可以超越牠。其具體訴求即是廢除動物農場與[[動物實驗|動物實驗]]，甚至反對任何動物利用，包括養[[寵物|寵物]]。<ref name="動物權" />

=== 中西異同 ===
上述內容會讓人以為動物福利是[[西方文化|西方文化]]獨有[[概念|概念]]。如探討傳統[[佛教|佛教]]傳統，將發現佛教比[[猶太教|猶太教]]、[[基督教|基督教]]或[[伊斯蘭教|伊斯蘭教]]，更加重視對動物的關懷。在西方哲人將動物納入[[倫理學|倫理學]]討論範疇之前，[[莊子|莊子]]等思想家就已經主張，[[愛|愛]]不只存在人與人之間，且應滲透到所有[[眾生|眾生]]之間。如今[[中國|中國]]有自己的[[動物權利運動|動物權利運動]]推廣者，有跡象表明，他們的訴求已開始受到重視。<ref name="道德進步與動物福利">{{Cite web |url = https://www.abc.net.au/religion/moral-progress-and-animal-welfare/10101318 |title = Moral Progress and Animal Welfare |author = Peter Singer |date = 2011-07-14 |publisher = Australian Broadcasting Corporation |language = en |accessdate = 2020-07-12 |quote = In light - perhaps one should say darkness - of such images, it is sometimes suggested that animal welfare is exclusively a Western concern. But that is implausible, given that Buddhist tradition places more emphasis on concern for animals than Judaism, Christianity, or Islam. Long before Western philosophers included animals in their ethics, Chinese philosophers like Zhuangzi said that love should permeate relations not only between humans, but between all sentient beings. Nowadays, China has its own animal-rights campaigners, and there are signs that their message is beginning to be heard. |archive-date = 2020-11-13 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201113055536/https://www.abc.net.au/religion/moral-progress-and-animal-welfare/10101318 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

以[[儒家|儒家]]為例，仁愛的對象不只包括人，也包含與人共生的動物。 《[[論語|論語]]·述而》：「子釣而不綱，弋不射宿」，[[孔子|孔子]]將對待動物的態度納入[[仁|仁]]的教化，並從中檢驗[[學生|學生]]德行的高尚與否、寬厚與否。許多朝代的法令均能見到動物保護的影子。例如：[[西周|西周]]頒布《伐崇令》中的「毋動六畜」，禁止傷害家畜、野生動物在內的所有動物。[[元朝|元朝]]《[[大扎撒|大扎撒]]》規定，任何人往躺在地上的動物身上[[小便|小便]]將被處以[[刑罰|刑罰]]。[[晚清|晚清]]時期，京師外城巡警總廳於1906年制定《管理大車規則》，其中第五條規定：「不准虐待[[牲口|牲口]]。」這是[[虐待|虐待]]一詞，首次由人延伸至動物。<ref>{{cite news |language = zh-cn |author = 孙安清 |coauthors = 北美小象君 |url = https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_7441239 |title = 动物福利入法呼声再起 |publisher = 上海东方报业有限公司 |pages =  |date = 2020-05-18 |accessdate = 2020-08-03 |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918032721/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_7441239 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

== 動物福利科學 ==
[[File:Lab_animal_care.jpg|alt=]]
基礎從[[獸醫學|獸醫學]]、[[畜牧學|畜牧學]]分化而來。也是獸醫、畜牧學、[[動物行為|動物行為]]、心理、生理學，以及野生生物學、[[免疫學|免疫學]]、[[神經生物學|神經生物學]]、新陳代謝學，暨[[社會心理學|社會心理學]]的科際整合。<ref name="EAST" />

動物權、動物福利因為牽涉到非人類動物的道德利益，為顧及立論正確性、可信度，不能對動物感覺做[[擬人化|擬人化]]（anthropomorphism）臆測，故須有實證科學，消除擬人化偏差。有鑑於此，動物福利學者特別強調研究，應從動物生理（例如：焦慮時，[[血液|血液]]生化值的變化）、心理（痛、恐懼時，[[行為學|行為學]]的定量與定性計數）、自然（各物種的行為偏好等）三項基礎做立論根據。<ref>{{Cite journal |author= 費昌勇 |author2= 楊書瑋 |author3=  |url= http://www.airitilibrary.com/Publication/alDetailedMesh?DocID=10282483-201110-201210020017-201210020017-75-103 |title= 動物權與動物對待 |journal= 應用倫理評論 |year= 2011 |volume=  |issue=  |pages= 75－103 |access-date= 2020-06-28 |archive-date= 2020-09-15 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200915054451/http://www.airitilibrary.com/Publication/alDetailedMesh?DocID=10282483-201110-201210020017-201210020017-75-103 |dead-url= no }}</ref>許多人誤解[[金魚|金魚]]只有三秒[[記憶|記憶]]，科學家如何評估水生動物的智能、[[情感|情感]]與痛苦呢？[[國立中山大學|國立中山大學]]生命科學系副教授顏聖紘表示，許多研究早指出魚類具有高度智能、學習能力，有些類群甚至比陸生動物還要傑出，部分魚類證實有[[自我|自我]]認知、[[工具|工具]]使用，有社群生活與[[社會結構|社會結構]]。他認為，人們對待[[動物|動物]]與[[食物|食物]]的方式不同，只是取決對牠的[[偏見|偏見]]與偏愛，這根本不是科學知識，而是人的[[問題|問題]]。<ref name="水生動物福利" />

=== 專業期刊 ===
*〈人類與動物關係學（Anthrozoos）〉<ref name="EAST" />
*〈動物福利（Animal Welfare）〉<ref name="EAST" />
*〈動物與社會（Society & Animals）〉<ref name="EAST" />
*〈應用動物福利科學（Journal of Applied Animal Welfare Science）〉<ref name="EAST" />

[[雪梨大學|雪梨大學]]博士生亞歷山德拉·格林在《[[科學報告|科學報告]]（Scientific Reports）》發表了一篇[[論文|論文]]，證實[[乳牛|乳牛]]發出[[聲音|聲音]]有其意義。格林的指導教授 Cameron Clark 表示，此研究具有啓發性，可創建屬於牛的[[Google翻譯|Google翻譯]]。格林表示：「我們希望通過了解這些聲音，農民能夠調適牛的[[情緒|情緒]]狀態，藉此改善動物福利。通過了解這些聲音[[特徵|特徵]]，農民就可以識別出牛群中，可能需要特別[[注意|注意]]的動物。」而研究最後也呼籲農民將有關乳牛聲音的知識納入日常飼養方式。<ref name="牛會說話">{{cite news |language = zh-tw |author = 黃敬翔 |coauthors =  |url = https://www.foodnext.net/science/technology/paper/5234403802 |title = 澳洲研究證實牛會說話！也許我們用「哞哞翻譯機」改善動物福利的未來不遠了！ |publisher = 食力foodNEXT |pages =  |date = 2020-01-11 |accessdate = 2020-07-27 |archive-date = 2020-09-15 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200915054014/https://www.foodnext.net/science/technology/paper/5234403802 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

亞歷山德拉歷經5個月、數百小時的時間，使用[[麥克風|麥克風]]記錄18頭[[荷尔斯泰因牛|荷尔斯泰因牛]]（Holstein-Friesian）的聲音，共採集到333個聲音樣本，再前往法國[[圣艾蒂安|圣艾蒂安]]（Saint-Etienne）與生物聲學家 David Reby 與 Livio Favaro 合作，藉以分析聲音特徵，進一步比較不同乳牛[[語句|語句]]結構的差異。研究主要設定了5種情境，分別是：『發情期』、『等待飼料前』、『被拒絕餵食』、『被迫與其他牛群隔開』、『與其他牛群隔開且無法看見對方』；前2種情境被歸類為「正面情緒（Positively valenced）」；後3種則是「負面情緒（Negatively valenced）」。結果顯示，乳牛的聲音表現在上述情境皆屬[[穩定|穩定]]，並可展現[[興奮|興奮]]、[[激勵|激勵]]、求歡或苦惱……等情緒，以便與其他牛群保持聯繫。<ref name="牛會說話" />

== 動物福利問題 ==
{{see|虐待動物|除爪手術|動物園|人道毀滅|生類憐憫令|捕鯨|海豚驅獵|鯨豚水族館}}

[[動物園|動物園]]的展示動物，通常在人造空間內被終身囚禁，導致動物福利議題經常被討論<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://wuo-wuo.com/report/57-comment/1106-hsinchu-zoo-opinion |title = 沒有籠子的動物園，圓了誰的夢？從改建後的新竹動物園談起 |author = 走近動物園 |date = 2020-01-10 |publisher = 窩窩 |language = zh-tw |accessdate = 2020-07-26 |quote = 若設計團隊無法正視在2020年的現在，哈根貝克在1907年為了展示「商品」就已經提出的「沒有籠子」，目前在園內的體現太過膚淺，充其量只能滿足參觀者在視覺上的潔癖，並沒有提升動物福利的直接效果（至少，在上方提及的案例中沒能看到）。即便我也理解在展示面消除人工痕跡的思維與其效益，但至少，在「新」新竹動物園的整體規劃上，過度顧忌籠子所象徵的「不自由」令園方在各個方面綁手綁腳，反而體現出真正意義上的不自由，還箝制了民眾對於不同動物園型式的思考。 |archive-date = 2020-11-01 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201101094051/https://wuo-wuo.com/report/57-comment/1106-hsinchu-zoo-opinion |dead-url = no }}</ref>。為解決問題，動物園的現代管理者就必須設出計符合[[人道|人道]]、豐富化的設施與飼養方式。<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.mdnkids.com/speak/detail.asp?sn=7076 |title = 動保小學堂　參訪動物園　探討動物福利 |author = 梁明煌 |date = 2019-12-25 |publisher = 財團法人國語日報社 |language = zh-tw |accessdate = 2020-07-26 |quote = 動物園展示的動物，通常被終身囚禁在很小的人造空間內，因此常有動物福利議題被討論。要解決這些問題，現代動物園管理者就必須嘗試設計出更符合人道、豐富化的設施與飼養方式。本文引導師生在參訪動物園時，能夠看出設計者為參觀者、飼養者及動物福利而設計的設施與原則。 |archive-date = 2020-09-15 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200915060353/https://www.mdnkids.com/speak/detail.asp?sn=7076 |dead-url = no }}</ref>

現代畜牧業起源於[[19世紀|19世紀]]後半，[[工業革命|工業革命]]造就人潮向[[都市|都市]]集中，為供應都會區食物，[[農產品|農產品]]生產開始改善效率。在歐美地區，首先計畫[[選育|選育]]高生產效率的[[家畜|家畜]]、[[家禽|家禽]]品種{{noteTag|name=動物育種註釋|1=在這之前的動物育種，主要為了提供上流社會展示會的觀賞動物，講究爭奇鬥豔的外觀，要求有品種協會登錄血統純正的系譜，因為這保證其後代可以保持和父母一樣的外貌。「純種才是最好」的迷思就一直流傳到現在，其實純種體弱多病，再加上許多「可愛」的外貌都是健康的負擔。目前純種狗的育種也是現代動保人士最關心的問題之一(Rooney and Sargan 2009)。}}，譬如：[[荷蘭乳牛|荷蘭乳牛]]、丹麥的藍瑞斯豬、英國的安格斯肉牛、義大利的來航蛋雞、美國的洛島紅（蛋肉兼用雞）……等，比傳統品種更良好的生產效率。以肉雞為例，一隻雞出售體重要達到3斤，早先的飼養期要半年以上；[[20世紀|20世紀]]誕生的洛島紅只需3個月，當時剛利用雜交生產的白肉雞2個月便可出售，改良到現在，體重僅35天就能達到3斤半{{noteTag|name=商業養雞註釋|1=台灣媒體與網路經常流傳「商業養雞都注射荷爾蒙才生長快速」完全不是事實。}}。現代畜牧業使動物生活在狹小空間、密集飼養，導致互相傷害，最簡單方法就是將雞剪喙控制啄羽，仔豬斷尾以防止咬尾巴，殘害動物肢體變為業界例行公事。禽畜產品價格便宜，一旦生病，農場主不會聘請獸醫{{noteTag|name=獸醫註釋|1=現代的獸醫學生大多以醫療貓狗等寵物為志向，很少以醫療畜禽為專業。}}，因為不敷成本。<ref name="NGO心視野" />

歐盟衛生和[[食品安全|食品安全]]專員 Janusz Wojciechowski 表示，歐盟即將出版《從農場到餐桌》戰略計畫，其中一項重點就是動物福利標章。歐盟執委會表明將修訂動物福利法案，其中包含更嚴格管制動物運輸，使法案更全面、易執行，並實踐更高水準的動物福利。因應德國代表團呼籲建立一個透明、統一的全歐盟動物福利標章，歐盟也正在研擬相關措施，希望藉此讓消費者安心。歐洲地區有許多企業或[[NGO|NGO]]正推行自家版本的動物福利標章。例如：法國 ÉtiquetteBien-Être 動物福利標章就被大力推行，該標章由四個動保協會（LFDA、CIWF、Oaba 和 Welfarm）與超市[[零售商|零售商]] Casino、家禽生產商 Fermiers de Loue 與 Fermiers du Sud-Ouest 三方共同合作，最近被[[家樂福超市|家樂福超市]]、Systeme U 零售公司、家禽品牌 Galliance 和[[農業合作社|農業合作社]] Terrena 採用。發表在《食欲》（Appetite）雜誌上的一項澳洲[[研究|研究]]就證實，這項計畫確實影響消費者的購買意願，[[雪梨大學|雪梨大學]]獸醫學院 Amelia Rose Cornish 總共訪問1千多名民眾、調查消費者喜好，發現提供標章等額外資訊，大幅增加人們購買福利產品的意願（與傳統福利產品相比）。研究人員還發現，這些標章還能提高民眾對「動物福利」的觀感及認識。<ref name="動物福利標章">{{cite news |language = zh-hant |author = 吳昱賢 |coauthors =  |url = https://animal-friendly.co/2020/03/13/animalwelfare-labels/ |title = 歐盟擬設“動物福利標章” 引導民眾提升觀念購買合規產品 |publisher = DPG動物友善 |pages =  |date = 2020-03-13 |accessdate = 2020-07-21 |archive-date = 2020-09-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918001722/https://animal-friendly.co/2020/03/13/animalwelfare-labels/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>

